<!-- About the Population of Turtles in Sri Lanka -->
<section class="hatchery">
    <h1>Turtle Population</h1>
    <p>In Sri Lanka</p>

    <!-- Hatchery's Picture -->
       <div class="hatchery-pic">
            <img src="./Images/sea-turtle-farm-and-hatchery.png">
        </div>

        <!-- 3 Paragraphs -->
       <div class="turtle-row">
        <div class="turtle-col">
            <h3>Threats</h3>
            <p>The turtle population in Sri Lanka is under threat from a variety of factors, including habitat degradation, pollution, and poaching. Many turtles are slaughtered for their meat, eggs, and shells, all of which are employed in traditional medicine and handicrafts. Furthermore, sea turtles are frequently ensnared in fishing nets, and inadvertent intake of plastic garbage can result in health problems and death.Conservation efforts can mitigate these threats and ensure survival</p>
        </div>
        <div class="turtle-col">
            <h3>Conservation</h3>
            <p>In Sri Lanka, conservation initiatives are undertaken to safeguard turtle populations and their habitats. Many groups are attempting to develop turtle hatcheries and educate the general public about the value of conservation. Additionally, efforts are being undertaken to encourage sustainable fishing techniques and prevent plastic waste in the oceans.Some organizations also work to rescue and rehabilitate injured turtles, releasing them back into the wild once they have fully recovered</p>
        </div>
        <div class="turtle-col">
            <h3>Hope</h3>
            <p> Despite the difficulties confronting Sri Lanka's turtle population, there remains optimism for the future. These magnificent species may flourish in their native habitats with continuous conservation efforts and improved awareness.It is critical to realize the importance of maintaining these species, not just for ecological reasons, but also for cultural and economic ones. The survival of Sri Lanka's turtle population is dependent on ongoing conservation and preservation initiatives.</p>
        </div>
       </div>   
</section>

